questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a Java-based web application using Spring Framework is experiencing frequent OutOfMemoryErrors. The application utilizes Spring's transaction management features and employs a mix of JDBC templates for database interactions. Upon inspecting the heap dumps, you notice a large number of retained objects, mostly of type java.sql.Connection, which are not being garbage collected. The relevant code snippet is: 
 @Transactional 
 public void performDatabaseOperation() { 
    Connection conn = DataSource.getConnection(); 
    // Perform operations... 
 }

You are debugging a production issue where a multi-threaded Java application is encountering performance degradation due to increased garbage collection pauses. The application utilizes a concurrent queue for inter-thread communication. The relevant code snippet is: 
 private static final Queue<Object> queue = new LinkedList<>(); 
 public void processQueue() { 
    while (!queue.isEmpty()) { 
       Object obj = queue.poll(); 
       // Process the object... 
    } 
 }

You are debugging a production issue where a Spring-based application using Spring Data JPA is experiencing memory leaks. The application has a service class annotated with @Service and @Transactional, and it uses an EntityManager to perform database operations. The relevant code snippet is: 
 @Service 
 @Transactional 
 public class MyService { 
    @PersistenceContext 
    private EntityManager entityManager; 
    public void performDatabaseOperation() { 
       // Perform operations using entityManager... 
       entityManager.clear(); 
    } 
 }
